<DocsLayout title="API Reference" description="PicFast REST API and MCP integration documentation.">
  <h1>API Reference</h1>
  <p>
    PicFast exposes a REST API at <code>/api/v1</code>. All endpoints require authentication unless marked as public.
  </p>

  <h2>Authentication</h2>
  <p>Authenticate using a Bearer token in the <code>Authorization</code> header:</p>
  <pre><code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;access_token&gt;</code></pre>
  <p>Get a token via <code>POST /api/v1/auth/login</code> or create an API token in the admin panel (tokens start with <code>img_</code>).</p>

  <h2>Public endpoints</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>GET /api/v1/config</code> — Site configuration</li>
    <li><code>GET /api/v1/version</code> — Version info</li>
    <li><code>GET /openapi.yaml</code> — OpenAPI spec (YAML)</li>
    <li><code>GET /openapi.json</code> — OpenAPI spec (JSON)</li>
    <li><code>GET /docs</code> — Interactive API documentation UI</li>
    <li><code>POST /api/v1/auth/register</code> — Register a new account</li>
    <li><code>POST /api/v1/auth/login</code> — Log in</li>
    <li><code>POST /api/v1/auth/refresh</code> — Refresh access token</li>
    <li><code>POST /api/v1/upload</code> — Guest upload (if enabled)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Upload</h2>
  <h3>POST /api/v1/images</h3>
  <p>Upload an image (authenticated). <code>multipart/form-data</code>:</p>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>file</code></td><td>file</td><td>Image file (required)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>album_id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Album ID to group the image</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>permission</code></td><td>int</td><td>0 = private, 1 = public (default)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>expires_in</code></td><td>string</td><td>Duration like <code>24h</code>, <code>7d</code></td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>strategy_id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Storage backend to use</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Guest upload</h2>
  <h3>POST /api/v1/upload</h3>
  <p>Same form fields as above, but works without authentication when guest upload is enabled (admin settings).</p>

  <h2>API tokens</h2>
  <p>For programmatic access, create API tokens via the web UI under Settings. Tokens are prefixed with <code>img_</code> and can be scoped to specific permissions. Use them as Bearer tokens in the Authorization header.</p>

  <h2>MCP Server (AI Agent Integration)</h2>
  <p>PicFast ships an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that lets AI agents like Claude and Cursor interact with your image hosting directly. The MCP server is published as <code>@picfast/mcp</code> on npm.</p>

  <h3>Quick setup</h3>
  <pre><code>npx @picfast/mcp</code></pre>
  <p>Configure in your MCP client:</p>
  <pre><code>&#123;
  "mcpServers": &#123;
    "picfast": &#123;
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["-y", "@picfast/mcp"],
      "env": &#123;
        "PICFAST_BASE_URL": "https://picfast.example.com",
        "PICFAST_API_TOKEN": "img_xxxxxxxx"
      &#125;
    &#125;
  &#125;
&#125;</code></pre>

  <h3>Available MCP tools</h3>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Tool</th><th>Auth</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>upload_image</code></td><td>Optional</td><td>Upload an image from a local file path. Supports guest mode.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>list_images</code></td><td>Required</td><td>List your images with pagination</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>get_image</code></td><td>Required</td><td>Get image details and share links (URL, Markdown, HTML, BBCode)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>delete_image</code></td><td>Required</td><td>Delete an image by key</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>get_usage_stats</code></td><td>Required</td><td>Check storage quota and usage</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>OpenAPI spec</h2>
  <p>The full API spec is available at:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>/openapi.yaml</code> — YAML format</li>
    <li><code>/openapi.json</code> — JSON format</li>
    <li><code>/docs</code> — Interactive Swagger UI for live testing</li>
  </ul>
</DocsLayout>
